  "final_text": "The project descriptor targets the NUCLEO-L476RG, so I'll pin its probe:\nDone \u2014 RCC read live off the NUCLEO-L476RG (attach-without-reset, state preserved). Full SVD-decoded dump saved at `\u2026/tool-results/btj1zgkhm.txt`. Here's my read of the clock tree:\n\n## Clock tree (BLINKY firmware, STM32L476RG)\n\n**System clock: 80 MHz from PLL \u2190 MSI**\n- `CR = 0x0300006B` \u2014 **MSION/MSIRDY=1**, MSIRGSEL=1, **MSIRANGE=6 \u2192 4 MHz**; **PLLON/PLLRDY=1**; HSI16 off, HSE off, CSS off\n- `CFGR = 0x0000000F` \u2014 **SW=PLL, SWS=PLL** (switch complete); AHB/APB1/APB2 prescalers all /1\n- `PLLCFGR = 0x01202801` \u2014 PLLSRC=**MSI**, PLLM=/1, **PLLN=\u00d740**, PLLREN=1, PLLR=/2 \u2192 4 MHz \u00d7 40 / 2 = **80 MHz SYSCLK**, so HCLK=PCLK1=PCLK2=80 MHz. PLLP/PLLQ outputs disabled\n- PLLSAI1/PLLSAI2 off (reset values)\n\n**Peripheral clock gates (the only ones enabled):**\n- `AHB1ENR = 0x100` \u2014 FLASH\n- `AHB2ENR = 0x1` \u2014 **GPIOA** (consistent with the LD2 blinky on PA5)\n- `APB1ENR1 = 0x20000` \u2014 **USART2** (the VCP UART)\n- Everything else gated off; no peripheral resets asserted\n\n**Other state:**\n- `BDCR = 0` \u2014 LSE off, RTC disabled; `CSR` low bits 0 \u2014 LSI off\n- `CCIPR = 0` \u2014 all kernel-clock muxes at default (USART2 \u2190 PCLK)\n- `CSR = 0x1C000000` \u2014 sticky reset flags: **PIN + BOR + software reset** recorded since last flag-clear (typical history after probe resets/flashing; clear with `RMVF` if you want a fresh baseline)\n\nIn short: a healthy, standard L476 80 MHz MSI\u2192PLL configuration with only GPIOA + USART2 clocked \u2014 exactly what the BLINKY firmware should look like. Note the bench has two probes attached (L476RG + N6570-DK); I pinned the L476's probe SN per the project descriptor. Want me to dump the N6's RCC too, or drill into any register?"
}